.SH YilmIndexVector
Compute the index of an 1D array of spherical harmonic coefficients
corresponding to \f[CR]i\f[R], \f[CR]l\f[R], and \f[CR]m\f[R].
.SH Usage
\f[CR]index\f[R] = YilmIndexVector (\f[CR]i\f[R], \f[CR]l\f[R],
\f[CR]m\f[R])
.SH Parameters
.TP
\f[CR]index\f[R] : output, integer(int32)
Index of an 1D array of spherical harmonic coefficients corresponding to
\f[CR]i\f[R], \f[CR]l\f[R], and \f[CR]m\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]i\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
1 corresponds to the cosine coefficient \f[CR]cilm(1,:,:)\f[R], and 2
corresponds to the sine coefficient \f[CR]cilm(2,:,:)\f[R].
.TP
\f[CR]l\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The spherical harmonic degree.
.TP
\f[CR]m\f[R] : input, integer(int32)
The angular order.
.SH Description
\f[CR]YilmIndexVector\f[R] will calculate the index of a 1D vector of
spherical harmonic coefficients corresponding to degree \f[CR]l\f[R],
angular order \f[CR]m\f[R] and \f[CR]i\f[R] (1 = cosine, 2 = sine).
The elements of the 1D vector array are packed by successive degrees,
where each degree lists the l+1 cosine terms and then the l cosine
terms.
The index is given explicitly by \f[CR]l**2+(i\-1)*l+m+1\f[R].
